<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <%- include("partials/head", {
    pageTitle: "Web Design"
  }) %>

  <body>
    <%- include("partials/nav") %>

    <main>
      <section class="page-title">
        <p class="eyebrow">Useful and visually clear</p>
        <h1>Web Design</h1>

        <p>
          Good design helps users understand the content and
          navigate a website easily.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="hero">
        <article>
          <h2>What Is Web Design?</h2>

          <p>
            Web design focuses on how a website looks and how users
            interact with it. A website should be clear, readable,
            and easy to navigate.
          </p>

          <p>
            Good web design uses colors, fonts, spacing, images, and
            layout to create a better user experience.
          </p>
        </article>

        <figure>
          <img
            src="/img/design.jpg"
            alt="Web design layout"
          >
        </figure>
      </section>

      <section class="cards">
        <article class="card">
          <span class="card-number">01</span>
          <h3>Color</h3>

          <p>
            Colors can make a website feel professional, calm, or
            creative.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <span class="card-number">02</span>
          <h3>Typography</h3>

          <p>
            Readable fonts help users understand the content better.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <span class="card-number">03</span>
          <h3>Layout</h3>

          <p>
            A clean layout helps users find information quickly.
          </p>
        </article>
      </section>
    </main>

    <%- include("partials/footer") %>
  </body>
</html>